9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 651, L.D. 1643, “An Act to Establish the
10 Maine Life Science Innovation Center”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13402 by striking out all of the first indented
12 paragraph (page 1, lines 26 to 28 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 'The Maine Life Science Innovation Center is established as a body corporate and
14 politic and a public instrumentality of the State, exercising public and essential
15 governmental functions. The center is an independent legal entity and is not a department,
16 agency or instrumentality of State Government for purposes of administrative law or
17 budgeting, and the debts, liabilities and obligations of the center are not debts, liabilities or
18 obligations of the State. The center shall leverage and expand the State's growing life
19 science sector by:'
20 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13403 in subsection 2 in the 2nd line (page 3,
21 line 18 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "15" and inserting the following: '17'
22 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13403 in subsection 2 in the 3rd line (page 3,
23 line 19 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "11" and inserting the following: '13'
24 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13403 in subsection 2 by striking out all of
25 paragraph C (page 3, lines 31 to 41 and page 4, lines 1 to 20 in L.D.) and inserting the
26 following:
27 'C. The members of the board who are not ex officio members are appointed by the
28 Governor and subject to confirmation by the Senate and must be individuals or
29 representatives of organizations that are in a position to advance the purposes and goals
30 of the center and are able to have a significant effect on improving the State's life
31 science economy as specified in the bylaws of the center. Consideration must be given
32 to the unique multidisciplinary nature of the State's life science sector, which leverages
33 innovations across human and animal health, marine biology, agriculture, forestry and
34 data science for the benefit of human, animal and environmental health. When making
35 appointments under this paragraph, the Governor shall consult with the board of
36 directors of the Maine Technology Institute and the board of directors of the Finance
