COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 651, L.D. 1643
317 Authority of Maine to ensure the alignment of those appointments with the State's
328 economic development strategies. Membership under this paragraph includes:
3 (1) A representative of a business in the State with fewer than 25 employees that
4 is involved in the life science sector;
5 (2) A representative of a business in the State with 25 or more employees that is
6 involved in the life science sector;
7 (3) Two representatives of nonprofit research institutions based in the State that
8 are involved in research and development in the life science sector;
9 (4) A representative of a private college, university, community college or trade
10 school in the State that is involved in the life science sector;
11 (5) A representative of a hospital in the State engaged in life science research, life
12 science innovation or life science workforce development;
13 (6) Two representatives of trade associations based in the State or other nonprofit
14 organizations that support the life science sector, including the executive director
15 of an association of life science companies, professionals and researchers in the
16 State;
17 (7) An entrepreneur in the life science sector;
18 (8) A representative of an institution that is a member of a collaborative network
19 of state educational and research institutions led by an internationally recognized
20 institution for biomedical research in the State;
21 (9) A representative of business investors or the banking or finance sectors;
22 (10) A member representing Washington County; and
23 (11) A member representing Aroostook County.
24 Members of the board who are not ex officio members serve 3-year terms.'
25 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13404 in subsection 1 in paragraph A by
26 striking out all of subparagraph (10) (page 5, lines 29 and 30 in L.D.) and inserting the
27 following:
28 '(10) Make payments in lieu of taxes and pay service fees as determined appropriate
29 by the board; and'
30 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13405 by inserting after subsection 3 the
31 following:
32 '4. Institutional affiliations, disclosure and recusal. Notwithstanding subsection 1,
33 an educational institution, research institution or nonprofit organization represented on the
34 board may apply for and receive funding or support from the center if:
35 A. The board member affiliated with the applicant institution or organization discloses
36 the affiliation in writing to the board prior to any deliberation, decision or vote
37 regarding the application;
38 B. The board member affiliated with the applicant institution or organization recuses
39 that board member from any participation in any discussion, deliberation or decision
40 regarding the application; and
