COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 651, L.D. 1643
1 C. Action on the application is taken by a vote of a majority of the disinterested board
2 members present and voting.'
3 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13405 by renumbering the subsections to read
4 consecutively.
5 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 397 in §13408 in subsection 1 by inserting after
6 paragraph H the following:
7 'After reviewing the report under this subsection, the joint standing committee may report
8 out legislation relating to the report in the same legislative session in which the report is
9 received.'
10 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
11 'Sec. 2. Maine Life Science Innovation Center; interim report.
12 Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 13408, the Maine Life
13 Science Innovation Center established pursuant to Title 5, section 13402 shall submit an
14 interim report to the Joint Standing Committee on Housing and Economic Development no
15 later than 180 days after all members of the center's board of directors have been appointed.
16 The interim report must include, but is not limited to, the following:
17 1. A description of the center's operations;
18 2. A statement of the center's proposed and projected activities for the ensuing fiscal
19 year; and
20 3. Recommendations regarding further actions that may be suitable for achieving the
21 purposes of the center.
22 After reviewing the interim report under this section, the joint standing committee may
23 report out legislation relating to the interim report in the same legislative session in which
24 the interim report is received.
25 Sec. 3. First board. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section
26 13403, subsection 2, paragraph C, the members of the first Board of Directors of the Maine
27 Life Science Innovation Center who are not ex officio members serve staggered terms, with
28 4 members serving for one-year terms, 4 members serving for 2-year terms and 4 members
29 serving for 3-year terms.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment amends the bill by:
34 1. Clarifying that the Maine Life Science Innovation Center is established as a body
35 corporate and politic and a public instrumentality of the State;
36 2. Adding a member representing a hospital in the State to the board of directors of the
37 center;
38 3. Directing the Governor to consult with the Finance Authority of Maine and Maine
39 Technology Institute when making appointments to the board of directors of the center and
Page 3 - 132LR2061(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

